  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"I envy you\"?",
  "response": "\"I envy you\" is a statement expressing a feeling of wanting something that someone else has or experiences. When someone says this, they typically mean:\n\n1. They admire or desire something you have, such as:\n- A skill or talent\n- A possession\n- An opportunity\n- A lifestyle\n- A personal achievement\n\n2. They wish they could be in your position or have your experiences\n\n3. They feel a sense of longing or slight resentment because you have something they want\n\nFor example:\n- \"You get to travel the world? I envy you!\"\n- \"You're so good at playing guitar. I really envy your musical talent.\"\n\nThe phrase implies a mix of admiration and a subtle feeling of wanting what the other person has.",
